title: Olympique Marseille vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Marseille have won three of their last four home games against Rennes in Ligue 1, each time without conceding a single goal. OM have kept 12 clean sheets at home against SRFC in the 21st century, at least two more than against any other team during this period. Marseille have finished just one of the last 12 Ligue 1 seasons with a defeat, losing 1-0 at Ajaccio on 3 June 2023.

title: Strasbourg vs Le Havre - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: The 39 meetings between Strasbourg and Le Havre in Ligue 1 have produced only three draws, a ratio of 7.7%. This is the lowest percentage of draws between two Ligue 1 teams among those who have faced each other 20+ times. Strasbourg have lost their last three matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, but they have been away from home each time, at Marseille, Lorient and Lyon in the last three years. At home, RCSA have gone three games to close a season without losing.

title: Nice vs Brest - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Nice have lost only one of their last eight Ligue 1 games against Brest. The last five Nice-Brest matches in Ligue 1 have produced just three goals, or 0.6 per game, the lowest average among meetings played in each of the last three seasons. Nice have won five of their last six matches to finish a Ligue 1 season, sharing the points in their most recent one. The last defeat of OGCN to end a season in the top-flight dates to 2017-18.

title: Czechia vs England - UEFA European Under 17 Championship - 2025
description: Albania will host the 2025 UEFA European Under-17 Championship finals, scheduled for 19 May to 1 June..The tournament will be the first under the new format, with Albania joined in the finals by Belgium, Czechia, England, France, Germany, holders Italy and Portugal who all emerged from qualifying. It will be the first UEFA final tournament ever hosted by the Football Association of Albania (FShF). Tirana’s Arena Kombëtare staged the inaugural UEFA Conference League final in 2022

description: Lens will face Monaco in Ligue 1 for the 108th time, the team that RCL have faced the most in the top-flight but also the one against which they have lost the most, with two defeats in the last three meetings. This is the third time in the last five years that the two teams have faced each other at Lens to close their season.

title: Lille vs Reims - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 34
description: Lille have won two games in a row against Reims in Ligue 1, after failing to win any of the previous four. title: Al Ahli Road to the AFC title 2024/25
description: Al Ahli celebrated becoming only the third Saudi club to win the Champions League, after record four-time winners Al Hilal and two-time champions Al Ittihad. Al Ahli have been crowned champions of Asia at the third attempt. Watch in this program how Al Ahli won the title.

title: Lion City Sailors (SGP) vs Sharjah FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Two - 2024/25 Finals
description: Lion City Sailors vs SharjahAFC Champions League TwoSeason 2024/2025FinalBishan Stadium Stadium

title: Al Ahli (KSA) vs Kawasaki (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2024/25 - Final
description: Al-Ahli will face Kawasaki Frontale for the first time in the AFC Champions League elite and for the first time against a Japanese team. Conversely, this will be Kawasaki Frontales second encounter against a Saudi team after defeating Al-Nassr 3-2 in the semi-finals. Al-Ahli have won only once in 5 matches against East Asian teams, with the win against Shenzhen 2-1 in the 2005 quarter-finals. This will be the fourth final between a Saudi team and a Japanese team in the AFC Champions League elite, the most common final matchup in the tournament. All previous finals were between Al-Hilal and Urawa Red Diamonds, with Al-Hilal winning one title in 2019 and Urawa winning two titles in 2017 and 2

title: AFC Womens Champions League 2024/25 - Final
description: AFC Womens Champions League 2024-2025 is the first edition of the Asias premier club womens football tournament organized by the Asian Football Confederation. Twelve teams, divided in three groups, participate in the group. The knockout stage will be played in a single-leg knockout format. The semi-finals and the final match will be played in centralized location.

title: Al Ahli (KSA) vs Kawasaki (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2024/25 - Final
description: Al-Ahli will face Kawasaki Frontale for the first time in the AFC Champions League elite and for the first time against a Japanese team. Conversely, this will be Kawasaki Frontales second encounter against a Saudi team after defeating Al-Nassr 3-2 in the semi-finals. Al-Ahli have won only once in 5 matches against East Asian teams, with the win against Shenzhen 2-1 in the 2005 quarter-finals. This will be the fourth final between a Saudi team and a Japanese team in the AFC Champions League elite, the most common final matchup in the tournament. All previous finals were between Al-Hilal and Urawa Red Diamonds, with Al-Hilal winning one title in 2019 and Urawa winning two titles in 2017 and 2

The event takes place from May 25 to June 8, 2025. As always, Roland Garros promises intense competition and unforgettable moments in the world of tennis.

description: The 2025 Roland Garros is the 129th edition of the French Open overall. Within the Open Era, which began in 1968, the 2024 edition is the 58th edition. The event takes place from May 25 to June 8, 2025. This iconic clay-court championship features top players from around the world competing for glory in singles, doubles, and mixed doubles categories. As always, Roland Garros promises intense competition and unforgettable moments in the world of tennis.

title: Creteil vs Cesson - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
description: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s 14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germains 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: World Sailing Show 2025
